<h1>Styles using external css</h1> 
<h2>Heading h2</h2> 
<h3>Heading h3</h3> 
<hr>
<p>This is a paragraph with a span tag to <span>highlight text</span>. <a 
href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/span">Know more about 
span tag.</a></p> 
<p id="text">External CSS is a form of CSS which is used to add styling to multiple HTML 
pages at a time. It helps to design the layout of many HTML web pages simultaneously. The 
external CSS is always saved with the .css extension, and through this file, we can change the 
complete style of our HTML web page.</p> 
<div> 
<p>Another paragraph inside a div. This text will be larger.</p> 
<img src="1.jpg" alt="Sample image"> 
</div> 
<p>Some additional text, and here's the time: <time datetime="2024-09-30T19:00 ">7:00 
PM, Sept 30, 2024</time>.</p> 
</body> 
